Date: Fri 28 Jan 2005
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Cource: The Canadian Press, Associated Press report, Thu 27 Jan 2005 [edited]
<http://www3.cjad.com/content/cp_article.asp?id=/global_feeds/CanadianPress/WorldNews/w012771A.htm>

Viet Nam; 3 New Cases (One of whom has Died) Reported
-------------------------------------------------
Viet Nam reported another avian flu death on Fri 28 Jan 2005, bringing the
human toll to 10 over the last month, officials said. A 32-year-old man
from northern Phu Tho province [presumably the same patient referred to as
a 30-year-old above - Mod.CP] died on Thu 27 Jan 2005 after spending 5 days
in Bach Mai Hospital in Hanoi, a doctor said on condition of anonymity. 2
other men, aged 66 and 30, from Hanoi and Hung Yen province, respectively,
tested positive for the H5N1 serotype of avian influenza virus and remained
in stable condition on Fri 28 Jan 2005, he said.
The man who died developed a high fever, coughing, and breathing
difficulties on 12 Jan 2005, said Nguyen Dinh Trong, Director of Phu Tho
Provincial Preventive Medicine Centre. The man's family raised poultry but
none of them has shown signs of illness, Trong said, adding there were no
avian influenza outbreaks reported among poultry in his village. Trong,
however, said the man was involved in the trade of poultry from infected
areas 6 months ago but had stopped since then, he added.
--
